arent":"159","text":"O → Onset (inicio gradual sugiere ACS)","guid":"pJ-SFJ8FTNKIZAkJO3gFRQ","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"P → Provocación/Palliación (esfuerzo, reposo, NTG)","guid":"I7YVx-1DRSSKkD6y1-Hriw","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Q → Quality (opresivo vs pleurítico vs punzante)","guid":"LtNu-SUaT4SqxgfcSP9Cbg","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"159","text":"R → Radiation (brazo, mandíbula, ambos brazos)","guid":"I3ecK6DlT2iH67TtFqZNTQ","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"159","text":"S → Site (subesternal vs localizado)","guid":"VXBDLW4lTQSCrEEKn3zYCQ","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"159","text":"T → Timing (>10 min sugiere SCA)","guid":"uYJri5BqQG-Jn6iLsTmkkQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"158","text":"Síntomas asociados","guid":"53EcPKYSQ5aNKmDhYkXDMg","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Diaforesis, náuseas, vómitos","guid":"OUxGzrCyTy6JDZAMLRMErw","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"Disnea, síncope, palpitaciones","guid":"4EGr3uA-TpOWY9B6YNlIfA","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"166","text":"Síntomas vagales","guid":"rmPYZk2fTkKQD92Yh2p8BA","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"158","text":"Historia previa","guid":"6aj3BZnJR-i7YzZE8GG5oA","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Cateterismo/angioTAC coronaria","guid":"5lb2vxqNQ8ygsN53pdcqfA","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"Estrés test previo","guid":"ITYi_vMuSVu6ItFms53P7Q","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"IAM o AI previos","guid":"PXsDbYSRTbivb-TTLhvhzA","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"170","text":"Nitroglicerina (respuesta no distingue isquémico)","guid":"IzzNzU29Q5SFKmbr0zAiPA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"175","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"PgIA6pdsS6y_YXEn5aAFJg","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"Irradiación a AMBOS brazos simultáneos = LR+ 7.1 (el hallazgo semiológico más potente del examen clínico)","guid":"xWtzggURQ2WvUd7kPkYTfA","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"Reproducibilidad con palpación NO descarta SCA completamente (LR+ 0.2-0.4, no 0)","guid":"YjXNyvwSTUqetmTZ4TMUNQ","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"Respuesta a nitroglicerina NO distingue isquémico de no-isquémico (mito clínico frecuente)","guid":"-vqbRxiKQAaM2jOS1Ne5pA","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"175","text":"Angina típica (Diamond-Forrester 3/3) → LR+ 5.8 es el predictor CLÍNICO más potente para EAC estable","guid":"vhkdX4HSTvGvSU-kU7lD2A","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"175","text":"ECG normal tiene LR+ 0.2 pero NO descarta SCA → repetir cada 10 min si dolor persiste","guid":"epWcQ9rhTPe0EvBRjB0roA","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"175","text":"En AM >75a la presentación atípica (disnea, delirium, síncope) es regla, no excepción","guid":"WvE3LHWtQSCaPSc4n8ycBw","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"175","text":"Sensibilidad ECG inicial para IAM <50% → biomarcadores seriados obligatorios","guid":"w9VAwlNgTWOZMqw_FSjxGQ","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"175","text":"HEART score ≤3 permite alta segura con MACE 1.7% a 6 semanas","guid":"QS6fMsaSStyUL3yTB0xBBQ","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"175","text":"Irradiación a brazo derecho (LR+ 2.9) > brazo izquierdo (LR+ 2.3) contra intuición popular","guid":"7qgAVIgqRWa4Ny_F_gPf4Q","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"175","text":"S3 audible duplica probabilidad IAM (LR+ 3.2) → auscultar dirigidamente","guid":"WMLUS_QvQoykU9aHEhQcPg","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"175","text":"DM, mujer y anciano → PEOR pronóstico por retraso diagnóstico","guid":"gH6jPiVXStGfhNi3v0bJ5Q","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"175","text":"Cocaína/anfetaminas → sospechar SCA independiente de otros FR","guid":"rF-9X8IvSVy5Qg7CQUtA1Q","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"175","text":"Combinación de hallazgos AUMENTA precisión (ninguno aislado es suficientemente potente para evitar estudio)","guid":"MfxhNnmKT_6QvyxwMZvQbA","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"175","text":"Referencias","guid":"4-yq7p85SGGkpT5pZpVmOQ","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"1. Panju AA, Hemmelgarn BR, Guyatt GH, Simel DL. Is this patient having a myocardial infarction? JAMA. 1998;280(14):1256-63.","guid":"i9qkvSAoR5CzV5tmWrHUrw","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"2. Swap CJ, Nagurney JT. Value and limitations of chest pain history in the evaluation of patients with suspected acute coronary syndromes. JAMA. 2005;294(20):2623-9.","guid":"PugapYLIRUuvAYdqBKidZg","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"189","text":"3. Chun AA, McGee SR. Bedside diagnosis of coronary artery disease: a systematic review. Am J Med. 2004;117(5):334-43.","guid":"Lv5N7oGnS6W7DlasYXbSyw","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"189","text":"4. Diamond GA, Forrester JS. Analysis of probability as an aid in the clinical diagnosis of coronary-artery disease. N Engl J Med. 1979;300(24):1350-8.","guid":"WPFOV_ODSyqJTYzFrvBj8g","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"189","text":"5. Six AJ, Backus BE, Kelder JC. Chest pain in the emergency room: value of the HEART score. Neth Heart J. 2008;16(6):191-6.","guid":"NBcpMnu2TfaomhnDUPo1uw","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"189","text":"6. Gulati M, Levy PD, Mukherjee D, et al. 2021 AHA/ACC/ASE/CHEST/SAEM/SCCT/SCMR Guideline for the Evaluation and Diagnosis of Chest Pain. Circulation. 2021;144(22):e368-e454.","guid":"eH_ecmU7RXSj1UBUdGUklQ","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"189","text":"7. Byrne RA, Rossello X, Coughlan JJ, et al. 2023 ESC Guidelines for the management of acute coronary syndromes. Eur Heart J. 2023;44(38):3720-3826.","guid":"bri4dNqeSA6d8jRU1zgNXg","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"189","text":"8. Thygesen K, Alpert JS, Jaffe AS, et al. Fourth universal definition of myocardial infarction (2018). Eur Heart J. 2019;40(3):237-269.","guid":"GwKW040WT6yfBcAc7bnv1A","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":197,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Cardiología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Cardiología","filename":"Dolor-Toracico-Anginoso","id":"map_163","resolved_references":[]}